msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:39
msgid "**Tokodon** brings the Mastodon federated social media platform to your fingertips, allowing you to easily read, post, and message."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:41
msgid "With version 23.04, communicating with your fellow Fediverse users is even easier, thanks to new features like the ability to see previous messages when replying and the ability to send polls to your followers. Tokodon's mobile version also features a dedicated search page to streamline the process of finding specific posts."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:43
msgid "![Tokodon poll](tokodon.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:45
msgid "Furthermore, version 23.04 enhances your privacy by allowing you to configure a proxy before logging into your Mastodon account. You can also view a list of follow requests, giving you more control over who you interact with on the Fediverse."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:51
msgid "![](https://apps.kde.org/app-icons/org.kde.audiotube.svg)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:53
#: content/fundraisers/yearend2024.md:54
msgid "[AudioTube](https://apps.kde.org/audiotube/)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:55
msgid "**AudioTube** brings all the music on YouTube to your desktop. This elegant and minimalistic player has undergone a visual redesign and also sports a smart new icon, as well as improved compatibility on mobile phones."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:57
msgid "You can search for music, make playlists, create playlists from your favorite songs, all songs from the playback history, or your most listened songs. You can also share links to your songs with others."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:59
msgid "![Audiotube](https://plasma-mobile.org/2023/03/29/this-month-plasma-mobile/audiotube-playlists-MPRIS.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:61
msgid "Finally, a major rewrite of parts of the code has made AudioTube lighter than ever."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:67
#: content/announcements/gear/23.08.0.md:155
msgid "![](https://apps.kde.org/app-icons/org.kde.neochat.svg)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:69
msgid "[NeoChat](https://apps.kde.org/neochat/)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:71
msgid "**NeoChat** is a native KDE app for chatting on Matrix. NeoChat improves its design with tweaks that provide a more compact layout and a simpler menu which works better for the collapsed room list."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:73
msgid "We have also improved the video controls, added a new command `/knock <room-id>` to send a *knock* event to a room, and you can now edit a prior message inline, within the chat pane."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:75
msgid "Other usability improvements include an overhaul of the keyboard navigation and shortcuts like <kbd>Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>PgUp</kbd>/<kbd>PgDn</kbd> that allow you to skip from room to room."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:86
msgid "**Spectacle** is KDE's screenshot and screen recorder app. This release features a total redesign of the user interface to make everything faster and easier to use. As part of this redesign, it's now possible to annotate screenshots directly from the rectangular region selection."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:88
msgid "![Spectacle rectangular selection](spectacle.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:90
msgid "In addition, Spectacle now offers built-in screen recording functionality on Wayland!"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:92
msgid "![Spectacle new ui](spectacle-new-ui.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:98
msgid "![](https://apps.kde.org/app-icons/org.kde.dolphin.svg)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:102
msgid "**Dolphin** is KDE's versatile and powerful file browser that not only lets you explore your local file system, but also remote servers and devices on the local network."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:104
msgid "In the area of file security and privileges, Dolphin now lets you configure how permissions are shown in the Details view. Dolphin has also become more flexible and now supports browsing Apple iOS devices using its native `afc://` protocol, file dialogs, and other file management tools. It can display the number of pages in a document in a metadata display, too."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:106
msgid "A much-requested feature is the possibility to run Dolphin in superuser mode, giving you full command of the entire file system. As this is quite dangerous, Dolphin does not allow itself to be run with `sudo` and tells you as much if you try. In this release, Dolphin will now also tells you how you can accomplish this goal in a fully supported matter using the new `kio-admin` add-on."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:108
msgid "![Open as administrator context menu](dolphin-admin.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:110
msgid "Despite these added features, Dolphin has not become slower. In fact, its code for counting directory sizes is faster, which improves performance, especially with manually-mounted network shares that aren't detected as such."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:116
#: content/announcements/gear/23.08.0.md:223
msgid "![](https://apps.kde.org/app-icons/org.kde.gwenview.svg)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:120
msgid "**Gwenview** lets you view your images and do some basic editing and annotations on them."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:122
msgid "When running on Plasma Wayland, you can now zoom in and out on images in Gwenview using pinch gestures on your touchpad!"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:124
msgid "Gwenview 23.04 includes changes that make it more predictable, like inhibiting sleep and screen locking during a slideshow only if it is in the foreground, or zooming smoothly rather than in steps when you use <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + scroll on a touchpad. Finally, we have fixed Gwenview's most commonly-experienced crash, often seen when rotating images quickly."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:130
#: content/announcements/gear/23.08.0.md:195
msgid "![](https://apps.kde.org/app-icons/org.kde.elisa.svg)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:134
msgid "**Elisa** is a smart and elegant music player available for both your computer and phone on most major platforms."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:136
msgid "In this release, Elisa allows you to collapse the large header area for a more streamlined appearance, if that's what you prefer. And now the *Frequently Played* view is a simple list of songs arranged by play count, doing away with the prior complicated time-based heuristic that was unclear and made the contents look random."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:140
msgid "As for playlists, Elisa now supports creating and opening `.pls` playlist files, and when you ask Elisa to open a playlist file with invalid paths, it skips them, shows you a message explaining what happened, and offers you the possibility to open the file so you can edit it and fix the broken paths."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:142
msgid "If listening to the radio is your jam, Elisa now includes more popular stations by default."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:148
#: content/announcements/gear/23.08.0.md:85
msgid "![](https://apps.kde.org/app-icons/org.kde.okular.svg)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:150
#: content/announcements/gear/23.08.0.md:87
msgid "[Okular](https://apps.kde.org/okular/)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:152
msgid "**Okular** is KDE's feature-rich document viewer."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:154
msgid "Following the trend of making KDE apps easier to use without sacrificing their flexibility, Okular's default toolbar layout has been tweaked for greater usability and relevance: now it includes the View Mode menu and the zoom and view buttons on the left side, with the tools on the right side. Additionally, the sidebar itself can now be relocated to either side of the window or un-docked to become a free-floating window."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:158
msgid "Another subtle tweak that makes using Okular more pleasurable is the zoom that now works smoothly rather than in steps when you use <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + the scroll on your touchpad or a high-resolution scroll wheel."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:164
msgid "![](https://apps.kde.org/app-icons/org.kde.filelight.svg)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:166
msgid "[Filelight](https://apps.kde.org/filelight)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:168
msgid "**[Filelight](https://apps.kde.org/filelight/)** gives you a clear and easy-to-understand overview of your disk space and usage. Version 23.04 comes with a list view on the left side of the window, providing a simple text-based method of viewing size information."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:170
msgid "![Filelight new sidebar](filelight.png)"
msgstr ""

