msgid "![](https://apps.kde.org/app-icons/org.kde.kdenlive.svg)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:180
msgid "The big news for KDE's powerful video editor is support for *nested timelines.* This new feature allows you to select several clips from your tracks, group them together, and then treat the group as one single sequence."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/23.04.0.md:182
msgid "You can edit the sequence, apply effects, and add transitions between nested and regular clips. You can later modify the nested sequence and the whole will update accordingly, making editing even more efficient and flexible."
msgstr ""

