#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:38
msgid "Many of the new features in [Dolphin](https://apps.kde.org/dolphin/) are designed to make it easier to access and manage files and folders that require administrative privileges. Visual cues, wizards to help install needed software, and menu options to elevate your privileges make it easier than ever to use Dolphin as a superuser."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:44
msgid "New usability features include:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:46
msgid "A new \"Move to New Folder‚Ä¶\" option that pops up when right-clicking a file, allowing you to create a folder and copy the file into it all in one go."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:48
msgid "Double-clicking the view background that triggers the \"Select All\" action by default."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:54
msgid "[Filelight](https://apps.kde.org/filelight/) is a complementary application to Dolphin, and can be installed directly from Dolphin by clicking the down arrow in the lower right corner of the main window."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:58
msgid "![Install Filelight directly from within Dolphin.](dolphin_install_filelight.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:61
msgid "Filelight helps visualize how much space your files and folders are taking up. Version 24.08 comes with a friendlier home page, and the Windows version (available from the Microsoft Store) has been redesigned to improve its overall appearance."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:66
msgid "![Filelight shows you the state of your hard disks.](filelight.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:68
msgid "Konsole 24.08 also comes with a brand new usability enhancement: if you need to bookmark something important in a long output, double-click the scroll bar to set a position marker. You can then quickly scroll back and locate it later."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:76
#: content/announcements/gear/24.12.0/index.md:75
msgid "Create"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:78
msgid "[Kdenlive](https://kdenlive.org) is KDE's professional video editor, and this new release is all about the curves."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:81
msgid "You can now use the brand new keyframe curve editor to customize effects, and easing methods (Cubic in/out and Exponential in/out) for fades."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:84
msgid "![New Effects easing.](kdenlive_effect_easing.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:86
msgid "To make things easier, we've redesigned the effects stack widget and improved the *Transform* effect, which now lets you select clips directly from the monitor. It also comes with a new grid, and improved design and behavior for the handle."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:95
#: content/announcements/gear/24.12.0/index.md:142
msgid "Travel"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:97
msgid "Coming to [Akademy 2024](https://akademy.kde.org/2024/)? Don't forget to install the updates for [Itinerary](https://apps.kde.org/itinerary/) and [Kongress](https://apps.kde.org/kongress/) and make your journey easy."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:101
msgid "Itinerary is KDE's travel assistant. It lets you plan and manage your trips, providing an overview of where you need to be and when. It keeps boarding passes, tickets, and health certificates all in one place, and the latest version adds more details, including seat information displayed directly in the timeline."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:107
msgid "![Itinerary shows seating numbers‚Ä¶](itinerary-timeline-seat-reservation.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:109
msgid "Once you arrive at your destination, it's time to fire up Kongress so you don't miss any of the sessions or activities. Kongress now makes things easier by providing indoor maps of the venue, so you not only know when and what's going on, but also where."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:114
msgid "![‚Ä¶And Kongress shows venue floorplans.](kongress_venue_maps.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:116
msgid "Both Itinerary and Kongress work on desktop and laptop computers and most mobile devices."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:123
#: content/announcements/gear/24.12.0/index.md:196
msgid "Communicate"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:125
msgid "[NeoChat](https://apps.kde.org/neochat/) is KDE's client for the Matrix chat system ‚Äî and KDE's official way of chatting. Version 24.08 increases your safety by allowing you to preemptively block invites from unknown users not in any rooms with you."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:130
msgid "[Tokodon](https://apps.kde.org/tokodon/) not only helps you read and post on Mastodon, but also manage your own server. Speaking of which, the version being released today can notify you of sign-ups on your server for better user management."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:135
msgid "![Tokodon feed.](tokodon_feed.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:137
msgid "For posting, you can easily attach images from the internet, quote other posts and pop out the text editor to comfortably compose your toot."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:140
msgid "When reading, Tokodon 24.08 supports scrolling up whole screenfuls of posts using the <kbd>PageUp</kbd> and <kbd>PageDown</kbd> keys."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:147
#: content/announcements/gear/24.12.0/index.md:236
msgid "Develop"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:149
msgid "Whether you want to help KDE implement features and fix bugs, or develop the next killer app, KDE's advanced text editor [Kate](https://kate-editor.org/) has you covered."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:153
msgid "Kate 24.08 improves its document formatting plugin with better support for bash, d, fish, Nix config, opsi-script, QML and YAML files. In related news, the Language Server Protocol (LSP) feature adds support for the Gleam, PureScript, and Typst languages."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:158
msgid "If you're working on a CMake-based project, the Project and Build plugin now allows you to open the build directory and get both files and targets."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:165
msgid "Surf"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:167
msgid "[Falkon](https://www.falkon.org/) is KDE's full-featured web browser. The new release implements many bug fixes and optimizations that make surfing the web with Falkon smoother, easier and safer."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:171
msgid "![KDE's Falkon web browser.](falkon.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:173
msgid "A new feature in 24.08 allows you to customize things that affect privacy and functionality on a site-by-site basis. Say you don't mind JavaScript on one site because the authors are trustworthy and it actually provides useful functionality, but you want to block it elsewhere for security reasons. You can now configure this in Falkon's _Settings_."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:183
#: content/announcements/gear/24.12.0/index.md:255
msgid "And all this too‚Ä¶"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:185
msgid "[Okular](https://okular.kde.org/) ‚Äî KDE's eco-certified document reader ‚Äî improves compatibility for fillable forms in PDF documents, gets a makeover for Windows, and adds a more usable zoom feature."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:188
msgid "[PlasmaTube](https://apps.kde.org/plasmatube/) ‚Äî a player for watching online videos from popular sites on your desktop ‚Äî adds an option to block sponsored sections in videos."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/gear/24.08.0.md:191
msgid "[Elisa](https://apps.kde.org/elisa/) ‚Äî our elegant music player ‚Äî gets a \"Play this next\" feature, and allows resizing of the sidebar and playlist panes."
msgstr ""

