#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:38
msgid "For Digital Artists"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:40
msgid "Plasma 6.2 includes a smorgasbord of new features for users of drawing tablets. Open _System Settings_ and look for _Drawing Tablet_ to see various tools for configuring drawing tablets."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:44
msgid "New in Plasma 6.2: a tablet calibration wizard and test mode; a feature to define the area of the screen that your tablet covers (the whole screen or a section); and the option to re-bind pen buttons to different kinds of mouse clicks."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:51
msgid "All this is built into Plasma; there‚Äôs no need to install new drivers or software from device manufacturers."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:54
msgid "And if your tablet is not yet supported, [‚ÄúWe care about your Input‚Äù](https://invent.kde.org/teams/goals/we-care-about-your-input) is a community-wide project that aims to provide support for unusual input devices. Let us know about your device so we can add it to the list!"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:59
msgid "Color Management"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:61
msgid "Related to the above ‚Äî and to ensure consistent colors across monitors ‚Äî we‚Äôve implemented more complete support for the Wayland color management protocol, and enabled it by default."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:65
msgid "We have also improved brightness handling for HDR and ICC profiles, as well as HDR performance. This will improve your experience when designing graphics, playing games, and watching videos."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:69
msgid "A new tone mapping feature built into Plasma‚Äôs KWin compositor will help improve the look of images with a brightness or set of colors greater than what the screen can display, thus reducing the ‚Äúblown out‚Äù look such images can otherwise exhibit."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:77
msgid "Power Management"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:79
msgid "Managing how much energy your system consumes and when are not only important for preserving its resources for when you need them, but also for using it in an environmentally responsible way."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:83
msgid "You can now override misbehaving applications that block the system from going to sleep or locking the screen (and thus prevent saving power), and you can also adjust the brightness of each connected monitor machine separately."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:87
msgid "As for the _Power and Battery_ widget, it not only shows how much power is remaining, but also allows you to adjust power profiles for different scenarios. New in Plasma 6.2: hold down the <kbd>Meta</kbd> (Windows) key and press <kbd>B</kbd> to cycle through the different options one at a time. A little badge of a leaf will show up on the battery icon to indicate when the system is in _power save_ mode, and a rocket for _performance_ mode."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:94
msgid "The battery widget showing power profiles"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:96
msgid "Discover and System Updating"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:98
msgid "Another thing we put you in complete control of is your software."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:100
msgid "Plasma‚Äôs built-in app store and software management tool, Discover, now supports PostmarketOS packages for your mobile devices, helps you write better reviews of apps, and presents apps‚Äô license information more accurately."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:104
msgid "You can also now choose to shut down the system after applying an offline system update, in addition to the existing option to restart afterwards."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:109
msgid "Since we made improving accessibility [a community-wide project](https://community.kde.org/Goals/KDE_For_All), we have increased the ways in which Plasma is easy to use for everyone."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:113
msgid "In Plasma 6.2, we overhauled _System Settings_‚Äô Accessibility page and added colorblindness filters. We also added support for the full ‚Äústicky keys‚Äù feature on Wayland."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:117
msgid "Color blindness assistant"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:120
msgid "UI/Visual Design"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:122
msgid "And of course, improving the look and feel of Plasma is always a high priority from one release to the next."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:125
msgid "In Plasma 6.2, we tweaked accent colors and the _System Tray_, reworked the _Widget Explorer_, and unified the look of dialogs and pop-ups. Finally, we improved the _Welcome Center_, sound effects, and actions."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:129
msgid "Many of these changes are subtle, but will provide a smoother and more enjoyable experience."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:136
msgid "And All This Too‚Ä¶"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:138
msgid "The _Weather Report_ widget now shows ‚Äúfeels like‚Äù temperatures, adds more information for BBC weather forecasts, and more."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:140
msgid "You can turn off window borders in the _Pager_ widget."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:141
msgid "The _Minimize All_ widget now minimizes only windows on the current virtual desktop and activity."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:143
msgid "You can now give custom names to your custom shortcuts."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:144
msgid "There's now an integrated cropping tool when setting a new user avatar."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:145
msgid "We‚Äôve added a once-a-year donation request notification ‚Äî please consider using it to show your love for Plasma by donating!"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.2.0.md:152
msgid "‚Ä¶and there‚Äôs much more going on as well: numerous stability and performance improvements, smaller visual changes, more Wayland protocols, and more! Check out the [complete changelog for Plasma 6.2](/announcements/changelogs/plasma/6/6.1.5-6.2.0)."
msgstr ""

