#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:68
msgid "Digital Art"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:70
msgid "We want to make Plasma the best platform for creativity, and Plasma 6.3 takes the next step in that direction by providing features that help artists optimize and customize their graphics tablets to their liking."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:72
msgid "The System Settings‚Äô _Drawing Tablet_ page has been overhauled and split into multiple tabs to improve how things are organized, and new configuration options have been added to each section:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:74
msgid "You can map an area of a drawing tablet‚Äôs surface to the entire screen area"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:75
msgid "We have refined the tablet calibration feature so that it produces more accurate calibrations"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:76
msgid "The stylus testing feature shows information about tilt and pressure"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:77
msgid "You can customize the pressure curve and range of a stylus to chop off the high and/or low parts"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:78
msgid "You can also re-map or swap the functions of the stylus‚Äôs buttons"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:80
msgid "![Configure your drawing tablet directly from Plasma‚Äôs _System Settings_ utility.](tablet_config.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:82
msgid "After finishing configuring your tablet, you‚Äôll be able to see what changed thanks to _System Settings_‚Äô ‚ÄúHighlight changed settings‚Äù feature, which works for most of the _Drawing Tablet_ page."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:88
msgid "Graphics"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:90
msgid "The most important news regarding graphics is a huge overhaul of how fractional scaling works. In Plasma 6.3, KWin makes a stronger effort to snap things to the screen‚Äôs pixel grid, greatly reducing blurriness and visual gaps everywhere and producing sharper and crisper images."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:92
msgid "This works at very high zoom levels as well, as KWin‚Äôs Zoom effect switches to a sharp pixel-perfect representation and overlays a grid on top of the screen. You can actually see how individual pixels look relative to other ones. Very useful for artists and designers."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:94
msgid "![KWin overlays a grid to better identify individual pixels at high zoom rates.](KWin_zoom.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:96
msgid "In the color department, screen colors are more accurate when using the _Night Light_ feature both with and without [ICC profiles](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ICC_profile), and KWin offers the option to choose screen color accuracy ‚Äî although this can sometimes affect system performance."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:98
msgid "A smaller but still nice detail is that widgets placed on the desktop are very slightly translucent, just like the popups of widgets placed on the panel:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:100
msgid "![Translucent widgets add a stylish touch to your desktop.](translucent_widgets.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:106
msgid "Hardware Monitoring"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:108
msgid "_System Monitor_ monitors CPU usage more accurately, and consumes vastly fewer CPU resources while doing it! If you‚Äôre using Plasma 6.3 on FreeBSD, you‚Äôre in luck: the System Monitor app and widgets can now collect GPU statistics on your system too."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:110
msgid "_Info Center_ also provides more information, exposing data about all of your GPUs as well as your batteries‚Äô cycle counts."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:112
msgid "Monitoring printers is equally easy, as each printer‚Äôs print queue is shown directly in the widget. The widget also shows a little spinner on any printers that are currently printing, so you can see at a glance which ones are in use."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:114
msgid "Plasma already includes a variety of background services that let you know when something has gone wrong and what to do about it. New in Plasma 6.3 is a service that detects when the kernel terminated an app because the system ran out of memory. The service shows a notification explaining what happened, and suggests ways of avoiding this issue in the future."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:120
msgid "Tools"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:122
msgid "Moving on to specific tools, Plasma 6.3‚Äôs _KRunner_ (the built-in search tool that also does conversions, calculations, definitions, graph plotting, and much more), _Discover_ (Plasma‚Äôs software management/app store application), and the _Weather Report_ widget all come with new features and improvements:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:126
msgid "KRunner and KRunner-powered searches now let you jump between categories using the <kbd>Page Up</kbd>/<kbd>Page Down</kbd> keys and <kbd>Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>Up</kbd>/<kbd>Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>Down</kbd> key combinations."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:130
msgid "A security enhancement landing in Discover highlights sandboxed apps whose permissions will change after being updated. This allows you to check on such changes in case you suspect any shady behavior."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:132
msgid "In a similar vein, you can now see whether apps are packaged directly by their developer, or verified by a trusted third party."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:136
msgid "If you‚Äôre a fan of the forecasts provided by [Deutscher Wetterdienst](https://www.dwd.de), you‚Äôre in luck: Plasma 6.3‚Äôs weather widget allows using this source for weather data."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:142
msgid "Usability"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:144
msgid "Plasma 6.3 makes things easy without ditching flexibility. If you prefer using a mouse with your laptop, you can now configure its built-in touchpad to switch off automatically, so it doesn‚Äôt interfere with your typing. Also, if you set up your machine as a network hotspot, Plasma generates a random password for the network so you don‚Äôt have to think one up."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:146
msgid "Finding help is easier in Plasma 6.3. A ‚ÄúHelp‚Äù category has been added to the launcher (the menu that tends to live on the left hand side of your panel), and we have removed the _Settings_ category entirely. Its contents have been merged into the _System_ category, reducing the number of categories that don‚Äôt offer meaningful grouping."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:148
msgid "![Help is readily available right from the launcher menu.](help_launcher.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:150
msgid "Speaking of menus, the default _Kickoff_ launcher menu now switches categories only when you click on them, matching the behavior of all other sidebar lists. However, if you preferred the old switch-on-hover behavior, it‚Äôs still available too."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:152
msgid "We have made things clearer by adding a _Show Target_ item to the desktop context menu for symbolic links, the digital Clock widget displays all events on days with more than five of them (giving you a complete view of upcoming commitments), and when you want to reboot into the bootloader menu the next time your machine reboots, the logout screen now indicates this."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:154
msgid "![The _Show Target_ option shows you what a symbolic link is pointing to.](Show_target.png)"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:156
msgid "To avoid overwhelming you with too much information, when notifications arrive while Plasma‚Äôs ‚ÄúDo Not Disturb‚Äù mode is engaged, exiting that mode shows the number of missed notifications, rather than sending them all in one giant torrent."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:158
msgid "Additionally, a subtle but important change: when you drag a file out of a window that‚Äôs partially below other windows, it no longer jumps to the top, potentially obscuring what you wanted to drag it into!"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:166
msgid "Finally, what would Plasma be without customization? To begin with, panels can be cloned! You can also use scripting to change your panels‚Äô opacity levels and what screen they appear on."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: content/announcements/plasma/6/6.3.0.md:168
msgid "In Plasma 6.2, we introduced symbolic icons in _Kickoff_‚Äôs category sidebar. Some people didn‚Äôt like that, so in 6.3 you can undo the change yourself: we modified the implementation to pull icons from the standard data source, allowing you to set them to whatever you want using the _Menu Editor_ app."
msgstr ""

